WEBVTT

00:08.074 --> 00:09.009
So, what's the plan?

00:09.009 --> 00:10.577
Are we going to
turn off the lights

00:10.577 --> 00:12.078
and jump out
and yell surprise?

00:12.579 --> 00:13.580
Oh, yes, Roz.

00:13.580 --> 00:16.416
Let's startle a man who
just had open-heart surgery.

00:16.416 --> 00:19.753
Sorry. I can't get used
to thinking of Niles as sick.

00:19.753 --> 00:20.754
Oh, Niles is great.

00:21.187 --> 00:22.255
All these exercises he's doing

00:22.255 --> 00:24.691
he's going to be just as strong
as he ever was.

00:24.691 --> 00:26.626
Here's the guest of honor.

00:26.626 --> 00:30.530
Niles, good to see you out and about.

00:30.530 --> 00:31.498
You look great!

00:32.031 --> 00:32.966
Thank you. Thank you.

00:32.966 --> 00:34.467
I'll tell you
it's good to be out

00:34.968 --> 00:35.535
after being cooped up

00:35.969 --> 00:37.370
in that apartment all week.
Hello.

00:37.604 --> 00:40.140
I never thought I'd grow tired of reading Flaubert.

00:40.140 --> 00:41.141
Oh, please.

00:41.141 --> 00:42.675
He's been parked on his ass

00:42.675 --> 00:44.177
watching The Young
and The Restless.

00:44.177 --> 00:45.078
FRASIER:
Niles!

00:45.078 --> 00:45.945
Not the soaps!

00:45.945 --> 00:47.313
You can't be serious.

00:47.313 --> 00:49.082
Well, I'm hardly hooked.

00:49.082 --> 00:50.984
They fascinate me as cultural artifact.

00:50.984 --> 00:52.886
I was just telling Gertrude.

00:52.886 --> 00:55.321
Their use of stock figures is reminiscent

00:55.321 --> 00:56.823
of thecommedia dell'arte.

00:56.823 --> 00:59.325
Esther is Punchinell
o, Victor is Flavio

00:59.826 --> 01:03.263
and Nicki, well, she's just the town pump.

01:04.998 --> 01:07.567
Now do you see why
I need my own telly, Daphne?

01:07.567 --> 01:09.569
You have your
own telly in Manchester.

01:10.070 --> 01:11.037
(uneasy laughter)

01:11.404 --> 01:13.406
Here's champagne and sparkling
cider for you Niles

01:13.773 --> 01:15.742
and help yourself to brunch
whenever you're ready.

01:16.109 --> 01:18.144
Word to the wise:
Stay away from the sausage.

01:18.578 --> 01:19.646
They're not sausages, Dad.

01:19.646 --> 01:21.581
They're soysages.

01:21.948 --> 01:24.017
Niles is on
a postoperative diet.

01:24.517 --> 01:25.885
We are trying
to support him.

01:26.186 --> 01:27.554
Oh, sorry. What about the bacon?

01:27.787 --> 01:29.856
Fake-un.

01:31.825 --> 01:34.861
Hey, everyone,
I'd like to propose a toast.

01:34.861 --> 01:36.830
To my family and friends:

01:36.830 --> 01:39.799
Your love and support
have been overwhelming.

01:40.133 --> 01:41.468
DAPHNE:
Oh, Niles.

01:41.668 --> 01:42.735
During my operation

01:42.735 --> 01:45.505
I was technically dead
for several minutes.

01:45.705 --> 01:47.707
Yes, we know, son. You told us.

01:48.108 --> 01:50.176
But it gave me a fresh
perspective on everything.

01:50.677 --> 01:51.678
It took a brush with death

01:51.678 --> 01:53.980
to remind me how lucky I am
to be alive.

01:54.214 --> 01:56.149
And Gertrude,
thank you for giving up

01:56.449 --> 01:57.517
the guest bedroom

01:57.517 --> 01:59.519
so that I don't have
to climb all those stairs.

01:59.519 --> 02:01.521
Oh, no, I'm happy
to sleep on that sofa bed

02:01.521 --> 02:03.389
with the hard metal frame.

02:03.690 --> 02:06.526
You have a nice, soft
bed in Manchester.

02:06.726 --> 02:08.728
Oh, Daphne, it's okay.

02:08.728 --> 02:10.229
Her bracing honesty reminds me

02:10.229 --> 02:12.232
that I'm alive.

02:12.732 --> 02:15.101
You, you... Oh, you!

02:15.401 --> 02:18.338
You are a treasure to me.

02:18.671 --> 02:21.207
I cherish every day
we're together.

02:21.641 --> 02:24.711
Oh, thank you, Niles.

02:24.711 --> 02:26.713
There may be others
around here

02:26.713 --> 02:29.415
who could benefit
from a near-death experience.

02:31.484 --> 02:33.419
Well, let's eat before
the fake-un loses its shape.

02:36.990 --> 02:39.893
Wow, Niles is really loving
life with a vengeance.

02:40.193 --> 02:41.728
I was the same way
after I got shot.

02:41.728 --> 02:43.763
First day back at the precinct

02:43.763 --> 02:45.265
I went around
hugging all the guys

02:45.265 --> 02:47.066
Telling them all I loved 'em

02:47.267 --> 02:48.201
How long did that last?

02:48.535 --> 02:51.604
Until they started
calling me "Martina."

02:52.038 --> 02:53.606
It is kind of weird

02:53.606 --> 02:56.943
seeing Niles so lovey-dovey
with Mrs. Moon.

02:57.243 --> 02:58.311
Believe me,
when you're in that state

02:58.811 --> 03:00.780
you can find something to love
even in the biggest jerk.

03:01.214 --> 03:03.750
Roz, I want to tell you you are a treasure.

03:05.151 --> 03:07.554
Maybe I don't say it often enough,
but you are.

03:07.554 --> 03:09.455
Shut up, Martina.

03:14.460 --> 03:16.963
(humming)

03:16.963 --> 03:17.964
Hi.

03:17.964 --> 03:19.365
I know that song.

03:19.699 --> 03:22.135
0."
Yes, Mozart's
"Symphony Number 4

03:22.435 --> 03:23.503
Molto allegro.

03:23.503 --> 03:25.004
I've just bought
this new recording for Niles.

03:25.004 --> 03:26.005
It is fantastic.

03:26.506 --> 03:27.507
I've never heard
such string articulation.

03:27.507 --> 03:28.875
Oh, I remember
what it is.

03:29.142 --> 03:30.710
It's that commercial
with the singing cats.

03:30.710 --> 03:33.713
♪♪ If your cat has a yearnin
g for tuna ♪♪

03:33.713 --> 03:35.215
♪
♪♪ Da-da-da, ocean buffet... ♪

03:37.116 --> 03:38.685
One of the cats was wearing
a tiny tuxedo.

03:38.685 --> 03:40.019
Good.

03:40.320 --> 03:43.790
So few cats dress
for the symphony anymore.

03:44.123 --> 03:45.692
Frasier, Roz.
Oh, hi, guys.

03:46.192 --> 03:49.195
Guess who just walked
a mile on the treadmill.

03:49.195 --> 03:50.964
Oh, way to go, Niles.

03:51.164 --> 03:53.233
The doctor says he's
in the 95th percentile

03:53.233 --> 03:55.735
of patients recovering
from bypass surgery.

03:55.735 --> 03:58.238
95th percentile!
That's wonderful, Niles.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.239
Well, now, Frasier

03:59.239 --> 04:01.241
good health
is not a competition.

04:01.241 --> 04:04.244
When you've heard time's
winged chariot hurrying near

04:04.244 --> 04:06.246
as I have,
every day is a gift.

04:06.246 --> 04:07.247
Oh, yoiks.

04:07.247 --> 04:09.182
What tone-deaf prankster
gave you this?

04:09.182 --> 04:10.950
You've heard it?

04:11.217 --> 04:12.285
Well, as much as I could bear.

04:12.785 --> 04:13.786
Did you hear what the conductor did

04:13.786 --> 04:15.288
to the andante?

04:15.288 --> 04:17.156
I just hope
he bought it dinner first

04:17.156 --> 04:18.992
Well, I couldn't
agree more, Niles.

04:18.992 --> 04:21.694
Frasier, you said
you loved that CD.

04:21.694 --> 04:23.963
Well, Niles has convinced me
otherwise.

04:24.330 --> 04:25.898
You know, I'm in
the mood for a scone.

04:26.399 --> 04:27.767
Help me pick one out.
All right.

04:28.034 --> 04:29.602
That was weird.
I'll say.

04:30.036 --> 04:32.939
Who can't pick out
their own scone?

04:33.206 --> 04:34.653
No. I mean you and Niles.

04:35.275 --> 04:37.844
Usually that would have been
a two-hour argument

04:38.344 --> 04:40.647
ending in tears
and cursing in Italian.

04:40.847 --> 04:42.315
I'm afraid those days
are over, Roz.

04:42.682 --> 04:43.683
What happened?

04:44.083 --> 04:46.119
Well, it's a long story.

04:46.119 --> 04:48.621
Okay. When Niles
was in the hospital

04:49.122 --> 04:51.658
and he was being wheeled
into surgery...

04:54.661 --> 04:57.497
he looked so frail and vulnerable

04:57.497 --> 04:58.398
so I..

04:58.398 --> 05:02.802
I took my case
to a higher power.

05:06.239 --> 05:09.275
Hello, God.

05:09.275 --> 05:12.312
It'’’s me, Dr. Frasier Crane

05:12.812 --> 05:16.316
Though I don't talk to you
as often as perhaps I should

05:16.316 --> 05:18.818
I want to thank you
for all the times

05:18.818 --> 05:20.820
you've indulged me in the past

05:20.820 --> 05:23.823
Although, I have yet to see
the inside of the Empire Club--

05:23.823 --> 05:25.825
just kidding.

05:25.825 --> 05:33.333
Anyway, today I ask you to look
after my brother, Niles Crane.

05:33.333 --> 05:37.337
I love him, even if I don't always show it.

05:37.337 --> 05:39.339
And I regret all the time

05:39.839 --> 05:42.342
he and I wasted
in petty quarrels.

05:42.342 --> 05:47.347
If you spare him, oh, Lord,

05:47.347 --> 05:51.684
I promise to cherish
every moment we have together.

05:51.918 --> 05:52.985
But, Frasier,
you don't think

05:52.985 --> 05:54.987
God is going to strike Niles down

05:54.987 --> 05:56.789
if you get in an argument,
do you?

05:56.989 --> 06:00.560
Well, technically,
the way it's structured

06:00.560 --> 06:02.061
he'd come after me.

06:02.061 --> 06:06.065
Seeing as how I was the one

06:06.065 --> 06:08.401
that initiated the deal, you see?

06:08.634 --> 06:09.702
If I'd had more time,

06:09.702 --> 06:12.505
I might have worded thin
gs differently, but...

06:12.705 --> 06:14.240
Oh, oh, uh, le
t's get this to go

06:14.240 --> 06:15.775
My soap starts in 20 minutes.

06:15.775 --> 06:18.277
Ashley might come
out of her coma today.

06:18.277 --> 06:22.782
You know, since your
recovery is going so well

06:22.782 --> 06:24.784
maybe we should check you out

06:24.784 --> 06:27.286
make sure all your equipment's
working properly.

06:29.288 --> 06:33.292
You're not talking about my exercise bicycle,
are you?

06:33.292 --> 06:35.595
The doctor said
it would be okay.

06:35.828 --> 06:37.897
If you need
a second opinion

06:37.897 --> 06:40.900
maybe Nurse Naughty
could make a house call.

06:43.903 --> 06:46.406
I could use a checkup.

06:46.839 --> 06:49.409
But I think we should
err on the side of caution

06:49.409 --> 06:50.910
In a few weeks, I have another stress test.

06:50.910 --> 06:52.412
Thank you.

06:52.412 --> 06:54.914
And if all goes well,
Nurse Naughty will be

06:54.914 --> 06:57.417
one satisfied
healthcare professional.

06:58.418 --> 06:59.419
See you.

06:59.919 --> 07:00.920
Oh, bye, guys.

07:00.920 --> 07:02.922
Oh, Niles, wait.

07:02.922 --> 07:04.424
Frasier says he thinks

07:04.424 --> 07:06.926
the string articulation
is really good.

07:06.926 --> 07:08.294
In this?

07:08.294 --> 07:10.129
Frasier, you know
I hold your opinion

07:10.129 --> 07:12.031
in highest regard,
but are you nuts?

07:12.031 --> 07:13.933
Perhaps, I am, Niles.
Thank you.

07:13.933 --> 07:15.802
Maybe you just need
to get your hearing checked.

07:15.802 --> 07:18.271
I'll do that.
Thank you, Niles.

07:18.271 --> 07:20.273
(loudly):
I'll see you later!

07:20.273 --> 07:21.774
(chuckles)

07:21.774 --> 07:23.276
Very amusing.

07:23.276 --> 07:24.777
I get it.

07:29.782 --> 07:32.118
Oh, oh, here they are.

07:32.385 --> 07:40.626
Frasier, Frasier,
tell them what you told me.

07:42.128 --> 07:45.131
I never thought
I'd live to see the day.

07:45.131 --> 07:47.400
Perhaps this is why
I was spared.

07:47.400 --> 07:51.471
Niles, how was your stress test?

07:51.771 --> 07:54.340
Oh, the doctor cleared me
to return to normal food

07:54.340 --> 07:55.675
and regular physical activity.

07:55.975 --> 07:57.910
Oh, Darling,
that's wonderful.

07:57.910 --> 08:00.613
Yes, yes.
In moderation, of course.

08:00.613 --> 08:01.948
Congratulations, son.

08:02.448 --> 08:03.316
Perhaps now, Niles

08:03.316 --> 08:04.984
we can get back
to the squash courts.

08:04.984 --> 08:07.186
Oh, I don't think so.

08:07.186 --> 08:09.722
But the doctor said
it was okay.

08:09.722 --> 08:11.491
Yeah, but shouldn't there
be more to life

08:11.491 --> 08:13.326
than competition for useless bragging rights?

08:13.326 --> 08:15.661
You didn't think they
were useless three months ago

08:16.162 --> 08:17.063
when you won.

08:17.063 --> 08:20.833
You bragged for three months.

08:20.833 --> 08:23.169
I've changed a lot
since then.

08:23.169 --> 08:25.171
The point is that
I have roses

08:25.171 --> 08:26.572
to stop and smell.

08:26.572 --> 08:28.474
I see. So, let me
get this straight.

08:28.474 --> 08:30.343
You're going to give up squash and smell roses.

08:30.643 --> 08:32.678
Poor Frasier.

08:34.679 --> 08:37.049
I hope that you don't have to go
through what I did

08:37.283 --> 08:39.184
in order to become
as wise as I have.

08:39.452 --> 08:42.020
You can still be wise
and play squash, darling.

08:42.455 --> 08:44.457
Daphne's right.
Go out, have some fun.

08:44.824 --> 08:45.892
But I am having fun.

08:45.892 --> 08:48.895
Since my incident,
birds sing more sweetly.

08:48.895 --> 08:50.363
The sky is so much bluer.

08:50.830 --> 08:52.665
Niles, it has rained
every day this week.

08:53.900 --> 08:56.302
I see rain differently, too.

08:56.302 --> 08:57.670
There's something I need
to tell you.

08:57.670 --> 08:59.972
It's something I've been thinking about.

08:59.972 --> 09:01.807
(thunder crashing)

09:05.645 --> 09:07.380
You were saying, Frasier?

09:07.380 --> 09:10.016
Nothing.

09:17.323 --> 09:19.091
My grandmother died
a couple of weeks ago

09:19.325 --> 09:20.693
and I feel bad
because I never told her

09:20.927 --> 09:22.461
how much she meant to me.

09:22.862 --> 09:24.430
Well, my heart certainly
goes out to you.

09:24.931 --> 09:27.767
Grieving is difficult enough
without those unresolved...

09:28.034 --> 09:29.101
Frasier, I'm sorry.

09:29.101 --> 09:31.504
But we have Dr. Niles Crane
on line two.

09:33.439 --> 09:35.441
I'm sure you all remember my brother Niles...

09:35.942 --> 09:38.945
from our last segment.

09:38.945 --> 09:41.414
I'm sure all my listeners join me

09:41.414 --> 09:44.450
in hoping he can get back
to work real soon.

09:44.450 --> 09:45.418
Thank you, Frasier.

09:45.418 --> 09:47.453
I just thought I'd add
the perspective

09:47.453 --> 09:50.790
of one who has ducked
the scythe of the Grim Reaper.

09:51.057 --> 09:53.025
By all means.
Go ahead, Niles.

09:53.326 --> 09:56.896
Your grandmother knows
how you feel.

09:56.896 --> 09:59.398
When I was briefly dead

09:59.398 --> 10:01.901
the overriding feeling I had

10:01.901 --> 10:05.237
was the love of my family
and friends.

10:05.538 --> 10:07.073
MAN:
Wow, so I shouldn't
feel bad?

10:07.073 --> 10:08.074
NILES:
Certainly not.

10:08.074 --> 10:10.042
Get out there
and live your life, Grant.

10:10.409 --> 10:12.411
Carpe that diem.

10:12.411 --> 10:14.413
Isn't that right, Frasier?

10:14.413 --> 10:16.482
I couldn't agree more, Niles

10:16.482 --> 10:18.918
We'll be right back
after traffic.

