10:28.828 --> 10:31.197
I'm beginning to regret
betting on the clown.

10:31.397 --> 10:33.966
Roz, I can't eat,
I can't sleep.

10:33.966 --> 10:36.435
I just lie in bed
awake at night

10:36.435 --> 10:38.938
mentally arguing
with Niles.

10:39.338 --> 10:41.407
And I win every time!

10:41.407 --> 10:42.608
Frasier,
this is insane

10:42.908 --> 10:45.478
Do you really think
something bad is going to happen

10:45.478 --> 10:46.979
if you break your deal with God?

10:46.979 --> 10:48.447
Oh, of course not.

10:48.447 --> 10:49.448
Well, maybe a little.

10:49.448 --> 10:50.416
I don't know.

10:52.618 --> 10:55.621
Roz, my brother could have died.

10:55.621 --> 10:59.158
I can't be ungrateful
to whatever higher power

10:59.158 --> 11:00.660
may have spared him.

11:00.660 --> 11:02.161
I just can't imagine

11:02.161 --> 11:04.163
that God would be upset...

11:04.163 --> 11:05.498
Roz!
Oh, he's God,

11:05.498 --> 11:07.833
Have you read
the Old Testamtent?

11:07.833 --> 11:09.235
He can be ruthless!

11:09.235 --> 11:12.138
Traffic's done.
You're on in five.

11:15.141 --> 11:16.642
Welcome back, Seattle.

11:16.642 --> 11:19.145
Oh, I see we have someone
on line two.

11:19.145 --> 11:21.647
Go ahead, caller. I'm listening.

11:21.647 --> 11:23.149
NILES:
Still me, Frasier.

11:23.149 --> 11:24.583
Say, I had some thoughts

11:24.583 --> 11:26.952
about your advice to Cynthia
from Tacoma.

11:26.952 --> 11:28.821
Speaking as one who has walked

11:28.821 --> 11:30.890
through the valley
of the shadow of death

11:31.357 --> 11:33.826
Cynthia,
I think diet and exercise

11:33.826 --> 11:35.394
should take care
of your problems.

11:35.861 --> 11:38.397
Nothing like a good
fat-free muffin...

11:41.834 --> 11:42.902
Hi, Daph,
I'm here for Niles.

11:42.902 --> 11:43.903
He's at your place.

11:43.903 --> 11:45.805
He said you were meeting
him there for dinner.

11:46.138 --> 11:49.108
I specifically told him
I would pick him up here.

11:49.108 --> 11:50.476
Sorry.

11:50.476 --> 11:53.479
Not bad enough he usurps
my radio show...

11:53.479 --> 11:55.281
What are you doing?

11:55.514 --> 11:58.084
Oh, you'll think I'm silly

11:58.084 --> 12:00.352
but I'm donating food to the poor.

12:00.686 --> 12:03.155
Why would I think that's silly?
What does that say about me?

12:03.456 --> 12:05.024
No, I was just going to say...

12:05.024 --> 12:06.392
I do my bit
for charity, you know.

12:06.692 --> 12:07.760
You have no idea
how many vacations

12:08.260 --> 12:09.695
I've bought
at silent auctions.

12:10.096 --> 12:11.664
No, that's not it.

12:11.664 --> 12:14.166
You see, when I found out
Niles needed heart surgery

12:14.166 --> 12:16.168
I felt so scared and helpless.

12:16.168 --> 12:19.672
So, I kind of made a vow
that if he came out okay

12:19.672 --> 12:22.174
I would spend more time
helping the less fortunate.

12:22.608 --> 12:25.611
A vow?
You mean like a promise to God?

12:25.978 --> 12:28.013
I know it must sound absurd
to you, a man of science.

12:28.547 --> 12:30.049
No, no.

12:30.049 --> 12:30.983
Now, when...

12:31.317 --> 12:33.385
exactly did you make
this promise?

12:33.786 --> 12:35.254
The night before his surgery.

12:35.554 --> 12:38.591
The night before, you say.

12:38.991 --> 12:40.459
Interesting.

12:40.826 --> 12:41.894
You say Niles
is at my place?

12:41.894 --> 12:43.395
Yeah.

12:43.395 --> 12:44.897
Excuse me.

12:44.897 --> 12:46.899
Keep up the good work.

12:50.903 --> 12:52.404
What's all this?

12:52.404 --> 12:53.405
Food for the poor.

12:53.405 --> 12:56.408
Oh, must be nice
to be poor

12:56.408 --> 12:59.245
and have people just
giving you food.

13:00.913 --> 13:04.083
Daphne, you were up
awfully late last night.

13:04.083 --> 13:06.452
Yeah, I was watching television.

13:06.452 --> 13:07.920
Were you?

13:07.920 --> 13:10.422
Or was that husband of yours
sneaking upstairs

13:10.422 --> 13:13.926
to demand you perform your wifely chore?

13:13.926 --> 13:14.927
I wish.

13:15.427 --> 13:18.330
He's still not ready to be
in the same bed with me.

13:18.330 --> 13:21.233
He's rich and you don't
have to sleep with him?

13:21.233 --> 13:23.102
Rub it in, why don't you?

13:25.004 --> 13:27.006
I know he's trying
to ease back into things

13:27.506 --> 13:30.009
but it's been weeks since
the doctor said he was okay.

13:30.509 --> 13:32.478
Well, isn't it obvious?

13:33.012 --> 13:36.482
The poor thing's probably
not feeling very attractive.

13:36.482 --> 13:42.388
He's all skinny and pale,
and now he has that scar, too.

13:42.721 --> 13:44.790
I don't think
that's it, Mum.

13:44.790 --> 13:47.293
I just think he's scared.
And I understand that.

13:47.293 --> 13:49.562
But how long are we going
to go on like this?

13:49.562 --> 13:51.764
Until you stop babying him.

13:51.764 --> 13:52.631
I'm not babying him.

13:52.631 --> 13:54.133
I'm just giving him
the time he needs.

13:54.633 --> 13:55.634
Oh, piffle.

13:56.035 --> 13:57.870
What he needs is
a swift kick in the bum.

13:58.103 --> 14:02.074
Look, you've got to seduce him.

14:02.408 --> 14:05.477
Use your feminine wiles.

14:05.477 --> 14:09.815
That's how your brother Billy landed Kevin.

14:10.082 --> 14:14.620
Well, sharing a cell helped.

14:15.054 --> 14:19.525
You know, maybe
I'll give that a try.

14:19.892 --> 14:22.461
When Niles walks into
that guest room tonight

14:22.461 --> 14:24.964
I'll have a surprise
waiting for him--

14:24.964 --> 14:27.967
candles, soft music,
a negligee...

14:27.967 --> 14:29.468
nothing too sexy.

14:29.468 --> 14:30.836
We don't want
to strain his heart.

14:31.170 --> 14:33.639
There's nothing wrong with your ego.

14:33.973 --> 14:35.507
Thanks for the advice, Mum.

14:36.008 --> 14:37.509
My pleasure, love.

14:37.910 --> 14:39.979
Oh, and since you and Niles
will be in the guest room

14:39.979 --> 14:41.480
I'll sleep in your room tonight.

14:41.981 --> 14:44.884
No sense in letting that
king-size bed go to waste.

14:45.251 --> 14:48.087
This time use a coaster
when you take your teeth out.

14:51.857 --> 14:54.393
Stop the tape.

14:54.393 --> 14:55.728
Who's he again?

14:55.995 --> 14:57.062
That's Diego

14:57.062 --> 14:59.031
the illegitimate son
of Sonya LaFontaine.

15:00.799 --> 15:03.369
He joined the army to avenge
the death of his brother.

15:03.869 --> 15:05.871
Although, frankly,
I'm a little worried about him

15:05.871 --> 15:09.174
I'm not sure he's figh
this war for the right reasons.

15:09.441 --> 15:11.510
Hey, you want some of this fancy dessert?

15:11.510 --> 15:12.511
It must be really good

15:12.511 --> 15:14.513
because Frasier told
me not to touch it

15:14.513 --> 15:16.015
No, no, thanks.

15:16.015 --> 15:18.450
I brought some of these
tasty rye flats

15:18.851 --> 15:22.888
in case I...
in case I feel peckish.

15:23.322 --> 15:24.890
They look like wood.

15:29.194 --> 15:30.763
Well, he di

15:30.763 --> 15:32.731
But, you know, I feel my tastes
have gotten simpler

15:33.232 --> 15:35.234
since I cheated death.

15:42.274 --> 15:44.076
It's hard to explain.

15:44.343 --> 15:45.411
Don't need to explain
to me, son.

15:45.911 --> 15:47.413
I know what it's like
to cheat death.

15:47.413 --> 15:48.747
That's true.

15:49.014 --> 15:51.350
Although I think I got a little
closer than you did.

15:51.350 --> 15:55.587
Oh, really?

15:55.587 --> 15:57.656
Well, let's see...

15:57.656 --> 16:02.628
I got shot by a gun
and you ate a bunch of cheese.

16:02.628 --> 16:06.098
I was clinically dead
for several minutes.

16:06.098 --> 16:08.334
I looked death
square in the eye.

16:08.334 --> 16:11.503
You may have looked him in
the eye, but I shook his hand.

16:11.503 --> 16:14.273
Really?
Well, I kissed him on the cheek.

16:14.273 --> 16:17.176
Well, I kissed him on the lips.

16:17.176 --> 16:19.945
Also, Death was a girl.

16:19.945 --> 16:22.848
Dad, I don't want to turn this into a competition.

16:22.848 --> 16:25.284
I'm just trying to embrace life to the fullest.

16:25.284 --> 16:27.753
Oh, would you
give it a rest.

16:27.753 --> 16:28.754
Excuse me?

16:28.754 --> 16:30.255
You haven't embraced a damn thing.

16:30.255 --> 16:31.256
All you're doing is yakking about

16:31.256 --> 16:32.758
feeling this and
experiencing that.

16:32.758 --> 16:33.659
You're not doing anything.

16:33.659 --> 16:36.362
You won't go back to work

16:36.362 --> 16:38.630
or play squash or eat
any of your favorite foods.

16:39.031 --> 16:42.601
I'm easing into things
until I'm back to normal.

16:43.102 --> 16:44.536
The doctor says you're there.

16:44.937 --> 16:47.006
Well, I'm just being
extra cautious.

16:47.006 --> 16:50.743
Sounds to me like you're afraid, son.

16:50.743 --> 16:53.512
Well, what if I am?

16:53.512 --> 16:55.014
Haven't I earned the right to be afraid?

16:55.514 --> 16:56.415
I could have died.

16:56.415 --> 16:58.317
I understand.
Okay.

16:58.317 --> 16:59.818
When I got out of the hospital

17:00.319 --> 17:02.154
I was terrified to take a risk.

17:02.154 --> 17:04.990
Just didn't want
to leave the house.

17:04.990 --> 17:09.494
Ducked for cover every time
a car backfired.

17:09.494 --> 17:14.967
I know my fears aren't rational.

17:14.967 --> 17:17.469
I know my heart is sound.

17:17.469 --> 17:20.472
I feel fine.

17:20.472 --> 17:22.241
But I felt fine
before this happened.

17:22.241 --> 17:24.309
How do I know

17:24.309 --> 17:25.644
that the same thing isn't.

17:25.644 --> 17:26.645
You don't know.

17:26.645 --> 17:28.647
That's exactly
what I came to realize.

17:28.647 --> 17:30.149
Life's a crap shoot.

17:30.149 --> 17:32.151
We could all go at any time.

17:32.651 --> 17:35.921
That's why we have to make the
most of whatever time we've got.

17:37.689 --> 17:40.192
Like sand through the hourglass

17:40.692 --> 17:43.529
so are the days of our lives.

17:43.529 --> 17:47.866
Okay, point taken.

17:49.868 --> 17:50.869
Thank you, Dad.

17:50.869 --> 17:52.337
Where are you going?

17:52.337 --> 17:54.206
To live my life.

17:54.540 --> 17:56.975
You forgot the rye flats.

17:57.309 --> 18:01.380
No, I didn't, Dad.
No, I didn't.

18:01.780 --> 18:03.182
Well, you're not
leaving them here.

18:10.522 --> 18:12.024
Good evening.

18:22.401 --> 18:23.902
Hello, God, it's me again.

18:23.902 --> 18:27.406
Dr. Frasier Crane.

18:27.406 --> 18:30.909
Listen, it seems that when
we made our little arrangement

18:31.410 --> 18:34.713
there was another deal in place.

18:34.913 --> 18:36.982
Now, I've had some experience
with double-booking

18:36.982 --> 18:39.485
and I know that the person
who books first

18:39.485 --> 18:42.287
always gets priority.

18:42.521 --> 18:44.590
So, as long as Daphne
keeps up her end...

18:44.590 --> 18:47.593
which she is, to the letter--

18:47.593 --> 18:50.596
it seems our little arrangement

18:51.096 --> 18:54.099
would be rendered null and void.

18:54.600 --> 19:00.439
Ergo, I am now going to yell
at my brother.

19:00.706 --> 19:03.775
Unless of course, you give me a sign.

19:09.448 --> 19:11.250
Very well, then.

19:11.250 --> 19:15.020
This is going to be sweet.

19:15.020 --> 19:16.421
(elevator dings)

19:16.755 --> 19:18.090
Niles!

19:18.290 --> 19:19.291
There you are.

19:19.291 --> 19:20.359
You're 40 minutes late.
Well, no matter.

19:20.859 --> 19:21.793
I have more important things to do.

19:22.294 --> 19:23.362
Not so fast, mister!

19:23.362 --> 19:25.330
You, sir, have been
insufferable for the
past few weeks.

19:25.330 --> 19:26.832
It might enlighten
you to know

19:26.832 --> 19:27.833
that your endless preaching

19:28.333 --> 19:29.835
has been nothing more
than a thin cover

19:29.835 --> 19:31.270
for your fear...
Yes, I know.

19:31.270 --> 19:32.704
I know, Dad just told me.

19:32.704 --> 19:34.573
And he was right,
I've been an ass lately.

19:34.873 --> 19:35.941
I'm really sorry,
but I have to go.

19:36.441 --> 19:37.276
My wife is waiting for me.

19:37.543 --> 19:38.610
Frankly, Frasier,

19:38.610 --> 19:39.912
I'm surprised you didn't
bring this up sooner.

19:40.212 --> 19:41.280
But...

19:50.289 --> 19:53.292
Huh.

19:53.292 --> 19:55.794
Well played, God.

20:02.301 --> 20:04.303
I'll see you at Easter.

20:21.320 --> 20:24.223
(high-pitched scream)

20:28.527 --> 20:29.828
Niles!

20:29.828 --> 20:31.029
What happened?

20:33.865 --> 20:34.833
Are you all right?
Yes.

20:34.833 --> 20:37.135
I just jumped into bed
with your mother.

20:37.135 --> 20:39.338
Oh, dear.
No wonder she screamed.

20:39.338 --> 20:41.506
That wasn't her.

20:41.506 --> 20:43.642
What were you doing in there?

20:43.642 --> 20:47.913
I just... wanted to...
take my wife in my arms

20:47.913 --> 20:49.414
and show her how much I love her.

20:49.414 --> 20:51.783
Are you sure you're ready?

20:51.783 --> 20:54.186
Trust me,
if my heart can take that

20:54.186 --> 20:55.554
it can take anything.

21:09.501 --> 21:11.503
♪♪ Hey, baby, I hear
the blues a-calling ♪♪

21:11.503 --> 21:14.006
♪♪ Toss salads and
scrambled eggs ♪♪

21:14.006 --> 21:16.742
Quite stylish.

21:16.742 --> 21:18.744
♪♪ And maybe I seem
a bit confused ♪♪

21:19.244 --> 21:21.046
♪♪Well, maybe,
but I got you pegged ♪♪

21:21.280 --> 21:23.315
(laughs)

21:23.315 --> 21:25.317
♪♪ But I don'’’t know what to do
 ♪♪

21:25.317 --> 21:29.354
♪♪ With those toss salads
and scrambled eggs ♪♪

21:29.855 --> 21:31.790
♪♪ They'’’re calling again
. ♪♪

21:32.157 --> 21:35.260
Good night, Seattle!
We love you!

